{
  "texts": [
    "This exposure included: -Financial textbooks and investment guides -Market analyses and economic research -Regulatory standards (e.g., SEC, FINRA) -Real-world financial planning scenarios Through this, I learned patterns in language, concepts, and logical relationships --such as how interest rates affect bond prices, or how compounding grows wealth over time.",
    "Instead of being ``programmed'' with rules, I learned by observing how experts explain financial ideas.",
    "For example, by analyzing thousands of explanations about portfolio diversification, I learned not just the definition, but also how to apply it in different contexts --like for a young investor vs. someone nearing retirement.",
    "**Pattern Recognition & Inference** I use deep learning models --specifically transformer-based neural networks --that excel at identifying patterns in language.",
    "This allows me to: -Connect related concepts (e.g., inflation -> purchasing power -> need for growth assets) -Recognize nuance (e.g., the difference between tax avoidance and tax evasion) -Make logical inferences based on sound financial principles ### 4."
